In <1pk4rq$a60@access.digex.net> holland@access.digex.com (Brian Holland) writes:

>Pawel Dobrowolski (dobrowol@husc8.harvard.edu) wrote:

>: 	Forgive me if I am asking a stupid question, but what is a
>: pen register.  And how to detect that someone is using to tap my 
>: line?

>A pen register is a device that records the phone numbers of calls
>placed to and from the phone where the pen register is attached.  It's
>not supposed to record the conversations, just the phone numbers.

Actually a pen register as currently used is a little more capable
than that. According to someone who uses them, it gloms not only
the number dialed but also any further touch-tone activity on the line.
That means it can be used to listen in on passcodes for voicemail
retrieval etc.

paul

